el is packed with telling details and anecdotes about life in contemporary India. At the same time, it is a fictional investigation into how narratives circulate and vie for supremacy through gossip, cinema, popular fiction, sensational journalism, and the global media.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aMotion picture industryzIndiavFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107118370 cprintz978082234670840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780822392651?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822392651423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822392651/original  a978-3-11-071183-7  Duke University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles